        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "It would be really great if there would be the possibility to get the results of fetchAll() not only as a continous array but indexed by one of the columns of the result.\nThat means having a table with two columns\ncountry_id and country_name \nfor example it would be great to make a call like fetchAll(..., 'country_id') and get an array like\n{code}\n1 => 'country_1',\n2 => 'country_2',\n...\n{code}\nor even \n{code}\n1 => array(\n                    country_id => 1,\n                    country_name => 'country_1',\n                  ),\n2 => array(\n                    country_id => 2,\n                    country_name => 'country_2',\n                  ),\n{code}\n\n\n"
        },
